column5: Nice job to this truck driver. i have no idea how he kept this on the road im not sure if i would be able to. tell me what you guys think.
they DO fly!?!?!?!  just not out of a WKRP helicopter though...

My buddies brother use to drive truck for Consumers Distributing and one night he had a great horned owl crash through the passenger side window and end up on the front seat. But that wasn't the worst part. Before he could get the truck stopped the darned thing came to and started freaking out inside the truck!!!!
has the price of shot shells inflated that much ?....now ill think of this photo when/if i should ever win another glass turkey
I was behind a woman in a honda civic that had the same thing happen. Lucky for me the turkey was still in pretty good shape, and she didn't want it  S.
Would be funny if the driver was drinking a Pepsi.
better yet...the turky was wearing a Pepsi ball cap
I swear, I thought they could fly- Les Nessman?
I think the drivers face says it all."The boss ain't never gonna believe this without a picture"
The placement of those feathers in the first picture is somewhat questionable, but it is wet outside.  Regardless, my dad hit an eagle with his rig, cost a bit of coin to get the body work done.
Wild Turkey and Coke is not a good mix
Rookie, your supposed to clip them in the head with your mirror.
I'd be sitting a little higher in the seat if that thing came crashing through my windshield! LOL
Nope his boss- Carlson." I swear to god, I thought turkeys could fly".
Did he try to revive it?
